### 1. Hardcoded Port — Lines 18–19 ⚠️

```js
app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server running on port 3000');
});
```

**Why it matters:** Hosting platforms (Heroku, Render, Railway, etc.) inject the port via `process.env.PORT`. Hardcoding `3000` will break deployments on those platforms.

**Fix:**
```js
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;
app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);
});
```

